Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into 1-inch-thick pieces. Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, dice @Yukon gold potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. (TIP: Peel first for a smoother texture.) Place in a #large pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve 1⁄2 cup potato cooking liquid; drain and return potatoes to pot. Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

Once carrots have roasted 10 minutes, remove #baking sheet{} from oven. Push carrots to one side of sheet. Carefully toss broccoli on empty side with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Return to top rack until veggies are browned and tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. (Save potatoes for another use.)

While potatoes cook, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

Heat #pot{} with drained potatoes over low heat; add half the @sour cream{4%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step) and @butter{1%tablespoon}.

Mash potatoes with a #potato masher{} until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Mushroom Gravy ==

Skip this step!

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and scallion whites; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer. Cook until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and remaining sour cream until melted and combined. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Use half the sour cream here. Save remaining sour cream for another use.

== Assembly ==

Heat pan with sauce over medium-low heat; add chicken and spoon sauce over top. Evenly top chicken with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}. Cover pan until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Divide chicken, carrots, and mashed potatoes between plates. Spoon remaining sauce over chicken and potatoes. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.